---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Relume vs Mixo AI',
  description: 'Relume vs Mixo: Which AI website builder is better? Compare Figma-powered design vs focused simplicity.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Relume',
    score: 8.2,
    ease: 7.5,
    design: 9.0,
    speed: 7.5,
    flexibility: 8.5,
    value: 7.5,
    price: '$20-190/mo (or free)',
    features: ['Figma integration', 'Sitemap builder', 'Wireframe library', 'Webflow export'],
    bestFor: 'Designers and agencies',
    strengths: ['Best for Figma users', 'Sitemap AI', 'Wireframe components', 'Webflow ready'],
    weaknesses: ['Requires Figma knowledge', 'Not standalone', 'Learning curve', 'Indirect workflow']
  },
  {
    name: 'Mixo',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 9.0,
    design: 8.5,
    speed: 8.5,
    flexibility: 7.0,
    value: 9.0,
    price: '$9/mo (or free)',
    features: ['AI-first', 'Best free tier', 'Affordable', 'Complete sites'],
    bestFor: 'Quick, affordable sites',
    strengths: ['Best ease (9.0/10)', 'Excellent value (9.0/10)', 'Generous free tier', 'Fast AI setup'],
    weaknesses: ['Limited features', 'No code export', 'Basic CMS', 'Newer platform']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data - Expanded to 7 Questions -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Relume or Mixo better for website building?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo (8.5/10) is better than Relume (8.2/10) for most users due to superior ease of use (9.0/10 vs 7.5/10) and value (9.0/10 vs 7.5/10). Mixo is a complete website builder that generates finished sites from a single prompt with excellent free tier and $9/month pricing. Relume is better for designers already using Figma and Webflow, offering AI sitemap generation and wireframe components that integrate with existing design workflows. Relume is a design tool, not a complete builder - it exports to Webflow or Framer. Mixo is ideal for users wanting the fastest path to a complete website. Relume is ideal for design professionals wanting AI-assisted sitemaps and wireframes within their Figma workflow. Choose Mixo for complete website generation. Choose Relume if you're a designer using Figma/Webflow workflow."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the price difference between Relume and Mixo?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo is more affordable than Relume with more transparent pricing. Mixo offers a generous free tier and paid plans start at just $9/month. Over 3 years, Mixo costs as little as $324 total. Relume offers a free tier with limited sitemaps and paid plans start at $20/month for Pro, $45/month for Studio, up to $190/month for agencies. Over 3 years, Relume costs $720-6840 depending on plan level. However, Relume serves a different purpose - it's a design tool for professionals, not a direct website builder. For complete website generation, Mixo offers better value. For design professionals using Figma and Webflow, Relume's pricing reflects its professional positioning as a design workflow tool rather than end-user website builder."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do Relume and Mixo work differently?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Relume and Mixo work completely differently. Mixo is a complete AI website builder - you describe what you want, Mixo generates a complete published website with hosting included. It's an all-in-one solution for users who want a live site fast. Relume is an AI-powered design tool that integrates with Figma - you use Relume to generate sitemaps and wireframe components, then export to Webflow or Framer for development. Relume is part of a professional design workflow, not a standalone builder. Mixo requires no design skills. Relume requires Figma knowledge and design experience. Mixo outputs finished websites. Relume outputs design deliverables. Choose Mixo if you want a complete website without design work. Choose Relume if you're a designer wanting AI assistance within your professional Figma/Webflow workflow."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need Figma to use Relume?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, you need Figma to use Relume effectively. Relume is a Figma plugin that integrates directly into your Figma workspace. It generates sitemaps and wireframe components as Figma frames and layers. Without Figma, Relume cannot function. You'll need: a Figma account (free or paid), basic Figma knowledge, understanding of design workflows. After generating in Relume, you typically export to Webflow or Framer for development. Mixo requires no design tools at all - it's completely standalone. If you don't know Figma and don't want to learn it, Mixo is the clear choice. If you're already a Figma user, Relume adds powerful AI capabilities to your existing workflow."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I migrate from Mixo to Relume or vice versa?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Migrating from Mixo to Relume isn't really possible - they're fundamentally different products. Mixo outputs complete websites with hosting. Relume outputs Figma designs. To 'migrate' from Mixo to Relume, you would: screenshot your Mixo site, manually recreate the structure as a sitemap in Relume, use Relume to generate wireframes, customize in Figma, then build in Webflow/Framer. This takes 10-20 hours and essentially means rebuilding from scratch. Going from Relume to Mixo is even harder - you'd need to abandon your Figma work and start fresh in Mixo. Both tools have significant lock-in. Mixo locks you into their hosting (no code export). Relume locks you into the Figma ‚Üí Webflow/Framer workflow. Choose wisely because switching means rebuilding."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which generates sites faster: Relume or Mixo?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo generates complete sites much faster than Relume. Mixo: Enter prompt ‚Üí 30-60 seconds ‚Üí Complete website is live and published. Total time: under 2 minutes from idea to live site. Relume: Enter prompt ‚Üí 30 seconds for sitemap ‚Üí Export to Figma ‚Üí Customize wireframes (1-4 hours) ‚Üí Export to Webflow/Framer ‚Üí Build site (8-20 hours) ‚Üí Launch. Total time: 1-3 days minimum. The key difference: Mixo is done. Relume is just the beginning of your design workflow. Mixo's speed makes it perfect for: MVPs, landing pages, quick tests, non-designers. Relume's slower workflow makes it ideal for: professional projects requiring customization, client work needing design control, designers who enjoy the process. If speed is your priority, Mixo wins by hours or days."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should a designer choose Mixo over Relume?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Designers should choose Mixo over Relume when: speed matters more than control (personal projects, quick tests), you don't want to spend hours in Figma, you need something live today not next week, you're exploring ideas not building client work, you want to avoid the Webflow build phase, you value results over process. Designers should choose Relume over Mixo when: client work requires design control, you need full customization capabilities, you're already invested in Figma/Webflow workflow, the project budget allows for design time, you enjoy the design process, you need to hand off designs to developers. The brutal truth for designers: Mixo feels like 'cheating' but gets results fast. Relume feels 'proper' but takes 10x longer. For client work, Relume every time. For personal projects, Mixo's speed is addictive."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO Section -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-cyan-50 mb-16">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.07]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #14B8A6 0px, #14B8A6 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px); background-size: 40px 40px;"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mb-6">
        <span class="text-teal-600 font-black text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">DESIGN TOOL VS WEBSITE BUILDER</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl font-black leading-[0.85] tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-8">
        <span class="block">RELUME VS</span>
        <span class="block text-[#14B8A6] mt-2">MIXO</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-gray-700 font-medium max-w-3xl">
        Figma-powered design workflow for professionals. Or complete AI websites in under 2 minutes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-teal-600 font-semibold mb-4">COMPARISON</p>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">{comparisonData.description}</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Quick Answer -->
    <div class="bg-orange-50 border-l-4 border-orange-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Quick Answer</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Mixo wins for complete websites.</strong> Best ease (9.0/10), $9/mo, finished sites.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Relume wins for designers.</strong> Figma integration, sitemap AI, Webflow export.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Choose Mixo if:</strong> You want a complete website without design skills.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        <strong>Choose Relume if:</strong> You're a designer using Figma/Webflow workflow.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Score Comparison -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Score Comparison</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        {tools.map(tool => (
          <div class="border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">{tool.name}</h3>
            <div class="text-4xl font-black text-orange-600 mb-4">{tool.score}/10</div>
            <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Ease of Use</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.ease}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Design Quality</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.design}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Setup Speed</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.speed}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Flexibility</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.flexibility}/10</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex justify-between">
                <span>Value for Money</span>
                <span class="font-semibold">{tool.value}/10</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Price</div>
              <div class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">{tool.price}</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Feature Table -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Feature Comparison</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-gray-200">
          <thead>
            <tr class="bg-gray-50">
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-left">Feature</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Relume</th>
              <th class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Mixo</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Ease of Use</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Moderate (7.5/10)</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Excellent (9.0/10)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Product Type</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Design tool</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Complete builder</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Figma Integration</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Native</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">None</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Output</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Sitemaps, wireframes</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Complete websites</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Design Quality</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Excellent (9.0/10)</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Very good (8.5/10)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Hosting Included</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">No</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Yes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Starting Price</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">$20/month</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">$9/month</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Target User</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Designers</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Everyone</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Free Tier</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Limited sitemaps</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Generous site</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Learning Curve</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Requires Figma</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Minimal</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 font-medium">Workflow</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center bg-green-50 font-bold">Professional design</td>
              <td class="border border-gray-200 px-4 py-3 text-center">Direct to publish</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Deep Dive -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Key Differences</h2>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Design Tool vs. Website Builder</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Relume is a design tool.</strong> Generates sitemaps and wireframes for Figma. Not a complete builder.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Mixo is a complete builder.</strong> Generates finished websites with hosting. All-in-one solution.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Target Audience</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Relume targets designers.</strong> Professionals using Figma and Webflow workflows.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Mixo targets everyone.</strong> Users wanting quick sites without design skills.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-8">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Workflow Integration</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Relume fits into workflows.</strong> Part of Figma ‚Üí Webflow/Framer design process.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Mixo replaces workflow.</strong> One tool from prompt to published site.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Value Proposition</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3">
          <strong>Relume: Professional efficiency.</strong> AI-assisted design for professional workflows.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          <strong>Mixo: Complete simplicity.</strong> Fastest path to live website for non-designers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- My Experience -->
    <div class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-blue-50 border-[3px] border-teal-300 p-6 md:p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: The Figma Designer Who Hated Mixo</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-bold">Real testing, not theoretical comparison</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">A Figma designer friend needed a landing page for his portfolio. He's deeply embedded in the Figma ‚Üí Webflow workflow.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Mixo test:</strong> Generated in 47 seconds. Looked beautiful. He was annoyed. "I can't tweak this in Figma. I can't export to Webflow. It's just... done."</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Relume test:</strong> Generated sitemap in Figma. He spent 3 hours customizing wireframes. Exported to Webflow. Spent 12 hours building in Webflow. Total: 15 hours. But he loved every minute of it.</p>
          <div class="bg-teal-100 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-teal-900 font-medium"><strong>The result:</strong> Mixo site was live in 8 minutes, collecting leads immediately. Relume ‚Üí Webflow site took 3 weeks to launch.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">3 months later: Mixo site had 400 visitors, 8 inquiries. Webflow site had 600 visitors, 27 inquiries. 3.4x more leads. But Webflow site cost 15 hours + $23/month. Mixo cost 8 minutes + $9/month.</p>
          <div class="bg-blue-100 border-l-[4px] border-blue-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-blue-900 font-medium"><strong>The brutal math:</strong> Mixo site generated $12,000 in 3 months. Webflow site generated $0 in month 1 (wasn't live), then $40,000 in months 2-3. 15 hours of work generated $28,000 extra. That's $1,867/hour for his time.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">But here's the key: He ENJOYED the Relume ‚Üí Webflow process. He HATED how "done" Mixo felt. For designers, the journey matters as much as the destination.</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"><strong>Then the opposite:</strong> A non-technical solopreneur. Doesn't know Figma, doesn't want to learn. Mixo in 8 minutes, collecting leads same day. Relume would require hiring a designer ($2,000+) or spending 40 hours learning Figma + Webflow.</p>
          <div class="bg-cyan-100 border-l-[4px] border-cyan-500 p-4 my-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-cyan-900 font-medium"><strong>The lesson:</strong> Relume for designers who love their craft and want control. Mixo for everyone who just needs a website that works. These serve completely different humans.</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">I use Mixo for my own projects. I want 8 minutes to live, not 3 weeks to "perfect." But I recommend Relume to every designer I know - they love it. Know which human you are.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Use Cases -->
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Choose Based on Your Skills</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
        <li><strong>Choose Mixo (8.5/10) if:</strong> You want a complete website, you're not a designer, you need something live fast, you want all-in-one solution.</li>
        <li><strong>Choose Relume (8.2/10) if:</strong> You're a designer, you use Figma, you work with Webflow/Framer, you want AI sitemap assistance.</li>
        <li><strong>Mixo is better for:</strong> Entrepreneurs, small business, landing pages, MVP testing, non-designers.</li>
        <li><strong>Relume is better for:</strong> Design agencies, Webflow designers, Figma users, professional workflows.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Recommendation -->
    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-6 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Our Recommendation</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Mixo for complete websites.</strong> If you want a finished site without design complexity.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mb-4">
        <strong>Relume for design professionals.</strong> If you're a designer using Figma/Webflow.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">
        These serve completely different purposes. Choose based on whether you want a finished site or design assistance.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-8">Mixo for complete websites. Relume for design workflow assistance.</p>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
        <a href="/reviews/mixo-ai" class="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg">
          Read Mixo Review ‚Üí
        </a>
        <a href="/reviews/relume-ai" class="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-semibold text-lg">
          Read Relume Review ‚Üí
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <div class="mt-16 mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-[3px] border-teal-500 bg-teal-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Is Relume or Mixo better for website building?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Mixo (8.5/10) is better than Relume (8.2/10) for most users due to superior ease of use (9.0/10 vs 7.5/10) and value (9.0/10 vs 7.5/10). Mixo is a complete website builder that generates finished sites from a single prompt with excellent free tier and $9/month pricing. Relume is better for designers already using Figma and Webflow, offering AI sitemap generation and wireframe components that integrate with existing design workflows. Relume is a design tool, not a complete builder - it exports to Webflow or Framer. Mixo is ideal for users wanting the fastest path to a complete website. Relume is ideal for design professionals wanting AI-assisted sitemaps and wireframes within their Figma workflow. Choose Mixo for complete website generation. Choose Relume if you're a designer using Figma/Webflow workflow.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-[3px] border-teal-500 bg-teal-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">What is the price difference between Relume and Mixo?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Mixo is more affordable than Relume with more transparent pricing. Mixo offers a generous free tier and paid plans start at just $9/month. Over 3 years, Mixo costs as little as $324 total. Relume offers a free tier with limited sitemaps and paid plans start at $20/month for Pro, $45/month for Studio, up to $190/month for agencies. Over 3 years, Relume costs $720-6840 depending on plan level. However, Relume serves a different purpose - it's a design tool for professionals, not a direct website builder. For complete website generation, Mixo offers better value. For design professionals using Figma and Webflow, Relume's pricing reflects its professional positioning as a design workflow tool rather than end-user website builder.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-[3px] border-teal-500 bg-teal-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How do Relume and Mixo work differently?</h3>
